01/08/2007
TIRANA, Albania -- President Bamir Topi met on Tuesday (July 31st) with the leader of the Socialist Movement for Integration Ilir Meta and with Parliament Speaker Jozefina Topalli. 
Topi and Meta discussed the reforms needed for Albania's eventual NATO and EU integration, while Topi and Topalli discussed projects to boost co-operation between the presidency and the parliament. 
(Albanian President Website, Balkanweb - 31/07/07)
